```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end
```

This function takes a DateTime object `dt` and an integer `bump` as arguments. The `bump` argument has a default value of 3. If the `bump` argument is not provided, the function will add 3 hours to the DateTime object. The function will throw an error if a Date object is provided instead of a DateTime object. The Dates.Hour function is used to add hours to the DateTime object.
